          "explanation": "\"In a normal infant, the Moro's reflex begins to fade at three months of age and gradually disappears at 4-6 months.\nWhen it persists beyond 6 months it indicates a delay in CNS development.\" ---------- Tachdjian\n\"Moro's reflex disappears by six months in a normal infant.\" ------------ Ghai"
