          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "IQ is defined by as the mental age divided by the chronological age multiplied by 100. In this case, a child of 6 years of age with an IQ of 50%, means that his mental age is that of a 3 year old child. At 3 years of age, a child can identify two colours. Ref: Essential paediatrics by OP Ghai, 6th edition, Page 543."
