          "explanation": "HSV infection may be acquired in utero, during the birth process, or during the neonatal period.\nIntrauterine and postpartum infections occur infrequently. \nMost cases of neonatal herpes result from maternal infection and transmission, usually during passage through a contaminated infected birth canal of a mother with asymptomatic genital herpes."
