          "explanation": "Here are the 15 most common signs and symptoms of vitamin C deficiency. Rough, Bumpy Skin. Corkscrew-Shaped Body Hair. Bright Red Hair Follicles. Spoon-Shaped Fingernails With Red Spots or Lines. Dry, Damaged Skin. Easy Bruising. Slowly Healing Wounds. Painful, Swollen Joints Reference: GHAI Essential pediatrics, 8th edition",
