          "explanation": "The total fetal cardiac output is approximately 450 mL/Kg/min. Approximately 65% of descending aoic blood flow returns to the placenta, and hence, only the remaining 35% perfuses the fetal organs and tissues. Ref: Nelson textbook of pediatrics 21st edition Pgno: 9260",
