          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Vaccine Recommended age of vaccination (1st dose) a. Varicella vaccine 15 months b. MMR vaccine 9 months c. Conjugated typhoid vaccine 9 months d. Pneumococcal polysaccharide vaccine Beyond 2 yrs age - As polysaccharides stimulate B-cells independent of T-cells, the pneumococcal polysaccharide is poorly immunogenic at <2yrs age & immunological memory is low - Hence, it is recommended beyond 2yrs of age.",
          "hint": "Topic: Vaccination schedule"
