          "explanation": "Lung abscess in children \n\nLung abscess is most likely to occur in -\n\ni)  Immunocompromized patients\nii) Those with recurrent aspiration\niii) Malnutrition \niv) Blunt chest trauma\nv) Complication of pneumonia\n\nOrganisms commonly causing lung abscess are -\nStaph. aureus  \nH.influenzae \nS. pneumoniae  \nPseudomonas\nE.coli \nKlebsiella                   \nOthers are → Nocardia, Legionella, Fungi (candida and aspergillus)"
