          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "newborns are at risk for hypoglycemia : Babies born to mothers with diabetes. Babies who are small for gestational age or growth-restricted. Preterm babies, especially those with low bih weights. Babies born under significant stress. Babies with mothers treated with ceain medicines such as terbutaline. Reference: GHAI Essential pediatrics, 8th edition",
